<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Goa</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">India's Jewel of <em>Beach Paradise</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Goa, India's smallest state by area but largest in charm and character, is a captivating blend of Portuguese colonial heritage and Indian culture. With pristine golden beaches stretching along the Arabian Sea, majestic churches standing as testaments to centuries past, spice-laden backwaters, and a vibrant cosmopolitan spirit, Goa epitomizes the perfect holiday destination. Known for its laid-back atmosphere, colorful festivals, world-class beaches, and delectable fusion cuisine, Goa attracts millions seeking sun, sea, and soul. From the serene North Goa with its bustling beach shacks to the tranquil South Goa with its untouched shorelines, from ancient temples hidden in valleys to Portuguese forts standing majestically, Goa is a paradise waiting to be explored. It's a place where Hindu traditions meet Christian celebrations, where spice traders' legacies blend with modern aspirations, creating a unique destination unlike anywhere else in India.</p>
</section>

<section id="weather" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lWeather">Climate &amp; Best Time</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="weatherTitle">When to Visit <em>Goa</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="weatherNote" style="margin-bottom:0">Goa experiences monsoon (June-September), winter (October-May) being the best season with pleasant weather. December to February offers perfect beach weather with mild temperatures and clear skies ideal for all activities.</p>
